.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "Simple Shell" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a basic UNIX command line interpreter written in C.
It displays a prompt, waits for the user to enter a command, and executes
the command using the execve system call.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes and handles
errors when commands cannot be executed.

.SH FEATURES
- Displays a prompt and waits for user input
- Executes commands with arguments
- Handles end of file (Ctrl+D)
- Works in interactive and non-interactive modes
- Error handling for invalid commands

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
./shell
.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.PP
echo "/bin/ls" | ./shell

.SH AUTHORS
Alexander Roman & Fabiola Burgos
